r Jesus Christ.\",\"foundingDate\":\"2024\",\"sameAs\":[]}"}}]],["$","main",null,{"style":{"maxWidth":860,"margin":"0 auto","padding":"3.5rem 2rem 5rem"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"borderBottom":"3px double var(--ink)","paddingBottom":"2rem","marginBottom":"3rem"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-ibm-plex-mono)","fontSize":"0.65rem","letterSpacing":"0.25em","textTransform":"uppercase","color":"var(--neutral)","marginBottom":"0.75rem"},"children":"Mission"}],["$","h1",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-playfair)","fontSize":"clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem)","fontWeight":900,"lineHeight":1.1,"letterSpacing":"-0.02em","marginBottom":"1rem"},"children":"About Plain Prophecy"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1rem","lineHeight":1.75,"color":"var(--neutral)","maxWidth":640},"children":"A Christ-centred resource for understanding biblical prophecy rigorously — without sensationalism as the goal is to produce faithfulness not fear and a deeper love for Jesus Christ."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"style":{"marginBottom":"3rem"},"children":[["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-playfair)","fontSize":"1.4rem","fontWeight":700,"marginBottom":"1rem"},"children":"What Plain Prophecy Is"}],["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"0.9rem","lineHeight":1.8,"color":"#3a3530","display":"flex","flexDirection":"column","gap":"0.75rem"},"children":[["$","p",null,{"children":"Most prophecy resources fall into one of two traps: they're either sensationalist end-times platforms that generate anxiety rather than understanding, or they're denomination-marketing tools where the conclusion is determined before the evidence is examined."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Plain Prophecy exists to do neither. We take the Historicist framework — the prophetic method of the entire Protestant Reformation — and examine it the way a historian would: by checking every claim against independent evidence, acknowledging where interpretive steps require inference, and keeping Christ at the centre of every timeline."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The Historicist reading of Daniel and Revelation was the consensus of Luther, Calvin, Tyndale, Knox, Newton, Wesley, and every major Reformer for nearly 300 years. Evangelical futurism is an 1830s innovation with origins in Jesuit Counter-Reformation polemic. The evidence is not close — but we let it speak for itself."}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"style":{"marginBottom":"3rem","background":"var(--cream-mid)","border":"2px solid var(--divider)","padding":"1.75rem"},"children":[["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-playfair)","fontSize":"1.2rem","fontWeight":700,"marginBottom":"1rem"},"children":"What Plain Prophecy Is Not"}],["$","ul",null,{"style":{"display":"flex","flexDirection":"column","gap":"0.6rem","paddingLeft":"1.25rem"},"children":[["$","li","0",{"style":{"fontSize":"0.87rem","lineHeight":1.6,"color":"#3a3530"},"children":"Not a fear platform — prophecy understood correctly produces faithfulness, not anxiety"}],["$","li","1",{"style":{"fontSize":"0.87rem","lineHeight":1.6,"color":"#3a3530"},"children":"Not sensationalist — we don't assign current world leaders to prophetic roles"}],["$","li","2",{"style":{"fontSize":"0.87rem","lineHeight":1.6,"color":"#3a3530"},"children":"Not infallible — we acknowledge genuine scholarly debate wherever it exists"}],["$","li","3",{"style":{"fontSize":"0.87rem","lineHeight":1.6,"color":"#3a3530"},"children":"Not people focused — the prophetic analysis applies to institutional systems, not individuals"}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"style":{"marginBottom":"3rem"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-ibm-plex-mono)","fontSize":"0.65rem","letterSpacing":"0.25em","textTransform":"uppercase","color":"var(--neutral)","marginBottom":"0.5rem"},"children":"Method"}],["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-playfair)","fontSize":"1.4rem","fontWeight":700,"marginBottom":"1.5rem"},"children":"Hermeneutical Principles"}],["$","div",null,{"style":{"display":"flex","flexDirection":"column","gap":"1rem"},"children":[["$","div","0",{"style":{"display":"flex","gap":"1.25rem","border":"1px solid var(--divider)","padding":"1.25rem","background":"var(--paper)"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-playfair)","fontSize":"1.5rem","fontWeight":900,"opacity":0.2,"lineHeight":1,"flexShrink":0,"minWidth":36},"children":"01"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-ibm-plex-sans)","fontWeight":600,"fontSize":"0.9rem","marginBottom":"0.35rem"},"children":"Scripture Interprets Scripture"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"0.84rem","lineHeight":1.65,"color":"#3a3530"},"children":"We never force a conclusion back into a text. The day-year principle is explicitly mandated (Num 14:34; Ezek 4:6) — not invented. Any prophetic anchor must be verifiable from the Bible itself before being checked against history."}]]}]]}],["$","div","1",{"style":{"display":"flex","gap":"1.25rem","border":"1px solid var(--divider)","padding":"1.25rem","background":"var(--cream-mid)"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-playfair)","fontSize":"1.5rem","fontWeight":900,"opacity":0.2,"lineHeight":1,"flexShrink":0,"minWidth":36},"children":"02"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-ibm-plex-sans)","fontWeight":600,"fontSize":"0.9rem","marginBottom":"0.35rem"},"children":"History Verifies Prophecy"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"0.84rem","lineHeight":1.65,"color":"#3a3530"},"children":"Genuine prophecy must have verifiable fulfilments independent of denominational tradition. We cite archaeology, secular chronology, and peer-reviewed history — not just church commentary. Every date is checked."}]]}]]}],["$","div","2",{"style":{"display":"flex","gap":"1.25rem","border":"1px solid var(--divider)","padding":"1.25rem","background":"var(--paper)"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-playfair)","fontSize":"1.5rem","fontWeight":900,"opacity":0.2,"lineHeight":1,"flexShrink":0,"minWidth":36},"children":"03"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-ibm-plex-sans)","fontWeight":600,"fontSize":"0.9rem","marginBottom":"0.35rem"},"children":"Christ at the Centre"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"0.84rem","lineHeight":1.65,"color":"#3a3530"},"children":"Every prophetic period anchors to who Jesus is: the Messiah of 457 BC, the Sacrifice of 31 AD, the risen High Priest of 1844, the Coming King. Prophecy is not a news ticker — it is Christology unfolded in time."}]]}]]}],["$","div","3",{"style":{"display":"flex","gap":"1.25rem","border":"1px solid var(--divider)","padding":"1.25rem","background":"var(--cream-mid)"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-playfair)","fontSize":"1.5rem","fontWeight":900,"opacity":0.2,"lineHeight":1,"flexShrink":0,"minWidth":36},"children":"04"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-ibm-plex-sans)","fontWeight":600,"fontSize":"0.9rem","marginBottom":"0.35rem"},"children":"Intellectual Honesty"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"0.84rem","lineHeight":1.65,"color":"#3a3530"},"children":"We acknowledge where the Historicist position carries genuine scholarly debate. A 9/10 is not a failure — it reflects where additional inference is required. We score both traditions against the same evidentiary standard."}]]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"style":{"background":"var(--ink)","color":"var(--paper)","padding":"2rem","textAlign":"center"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-ibm-plex-mono)","fontSize":"0.62rem","letterSpacing":"0.25em","textTransform":"uppercase","opacity":0.5,"marginBottom":"1rem"},"children":"The Central Texts"}],["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-playfair)","fontSize":"clamp(0.9rem, 2vw, 1.05rem)","lineHeight":1.8,"opacity":0.85